{% style %}
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;1,300;1,400&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500&display=swap');
{% endstyle %}

<div class="plekify-v6">

<!-- TWO PRODUCTS -->
<section id="itineraries" class="section">
  <span class="annot">What Plekify does</span>
  <div class="two-col">
    <div>
      <h2 class="sh">Itinerary design<br><em>&amp; commerce</em></h2>
      <p class="body" style="margin-top:.75rem">The AI pipeline designs itineraries from scratch or enhances ones already in Wetu — then syncs them to Shopify as browseable product pages with richer property detail, deeper day-by-day structure, and more navigable media than a standard Wetu layout. Guests can pay a deposit or structured instalments directly on the operator's site. For high-value journeys, Shopify handles commercial complexity that a simple payment link cannot: milestone billing, B2B agent pricing, multi-currency checkout, and payment terms for trade partners.</p>
      <div class="flow" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
        <span class="flow-node">Brief or existing Wetu itinerary</span>
        <span class="flow-arr">→</span>
        <span class="flow-node">AI pipeline</span>
        <span class="flow-arr">→</span>
        <span class="flow-node">Wetu upload</span>
        <span class="flow-arr">→</span>
        <span class="flow-node">Guest pays on your domain</span>
      </div>
      <ul class="feature-list" style="margin-top:1rem">
        <li>Design new itineraries or enhance existing ones</li>
        <li>Deposit &amp; instalment scheduling</li>
        <li>B2B agent tiers with negotiated pricing</li>
        <li>SEO on your domain, not wetu.com</li>
        <li>Dual client &amp; operator views</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div id="bookings">
      <h2 class="sh">Accommodation<br><em>booking</em></h2>
      <p class="body" style="margin-top:.75rem">Properties already run a property management system. Plekify connects to it via API — live availability, real-time pricing, and checkout happen on the property's own website, while the reservation is created in the existing PMS automatically. The guest never leaves the operator's domain. The operator's back office continues unchanged.</p>
      <div class="hl-box">
        <p class="body"><strong style="font-weight:400;color:#444">The handoff problem:</strong> Most properties direct guests to a third-party booking engine to complete a reservation. That moment — when the guest leaves the operator's website — breaks the brand experience and means the guest's contact details are captured by another platform, not yours. Plekify eliminates the handoff without changing how the PMS runs.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="body" style="margin-top:.85rem">ResRequest is live today, serving 400+ properties across 14 African countries. NightsBridge — the dominant platform in South Africa — and additional systems are on the integration roadmap. The architecture is built to connect to any PMS with an open API.</p>
      <ul class="feature-list" style="margin-top:1rem">
        <li>ResRequest — live now</li>
        <li>Further PMS integrations coming</li>
        <li>OTA &amp; channel management unchanged</li>
        <li>Guest data lands in your Shopify CRM</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THREE MODES OF AI ITINERARY WORK -->
<section id="ai-planning" class="section">
  <span class="annot">Three modes of AI itinerary work</span>
  <h2 class="sh">The AI does not replace the consultant.<br><em>It removes the ceiling.</em></h2>
  <p class="body" style="margin-top:.65rem;max-width:640px">A consultant's itinerary quality is bounded by memory, experience, and time. The pipeline has no such limits — it searches the full Wetu property database, cross-references Google Maps and each property's own site content, and works against hard constraints set by the brief. It operates in three modes:</p>

  <div class="modes-grid">
    <div class="mode-card">
      <span class="mode-num">01 — Design</span>
      <div class="mode-title">New itinerary<br><em>from brief</em></div>
      <p class="mode-body">A natural-language brief is the only input. The pipeline handles constraint detection, candidate discovery, route validation, commercial structuring, narrative writing, and direct upload to Wetu — then sync to Shopify as a bookable product. Brief to bookable in hours.</p>
      <span class="mode-tag">Full pipeline · 14 agents</span>
    </div>
    <div class="mode-card featured-mode">
      <span class="mode-num">02 — Enhance</span>
      <div class="mode-title">Existing Wetu<br><em>itinerary upgraded</em></div>
      <p class="mode-body">An existing itinerary in Wetu is passed to the pipeline. The AI evaluates every property selection against the full database — surfacing better-matched alternatives, filling gaps, improving routing, and freshening narrative — then uploads the improved version back to Wetu on behalf of the client.</p>
      <span class="mode-tag">Enhancement pipeline · On behalf of client</span>
    </div>
    <div class="mode-card">
      <span class="mode-num">03 — Publish</span>
      <div class="mode-title">Human design<br><em>made bookable</em></div>
      <p class="mode-body">An itinerary designed by a consultant in Wetu is synced to Shopify without modification. The AI adds no new selections — it enriches the presentation, structures the commercial layer, and publishes it as a product on the operator's own domain. The consultant's work, properly sold.</p>
      <span class="mode-tag">Sync &amp; publish · Commerce layer only</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hl-box" style="margin-top:1.75rem">
    <p class="body" style="color:#555"><strong style="font-weight:400;color:#333">On enhancement:</strong> Most Wetu itineraries were built at a point in time against the properties a consultant happened to know. The Wetu database has grown substantially since many of those itineraries were first assembled. The enhancement pipeline runs every leg against the full current database — a systematic upgrade that no individual consultant has time to perform manually, done programmatically and uploaded back into the client's Wetu account.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- AI PIPELINE DETAIL -->
<div class="ai-section">
  <span class="annot">Inside the pipeline</span>
  <h2 class="sh">From brief to bookable<br><em>in hours, not weeks.</em></h2>
  <p class="lead" style="margin-top:.65rem;font-size:14.5px;max-width:100%">The pipeline works against a verified intelligence layer built from the full Wetu property database, cross-referenced with Google Maps data and each property's own website content. Constraint detection, candidate discovery, route validation, commercial structuring, narrative generation, and direct upload to Wetu — each stage validated before the next begins.</p>

  <div class="ai-demo">
    <div>
      <p class="body" style="margin-bottom:.5rem">Hard constraints from the brief are enforced automatically across every leg, every candidate, and every recommendation — before a single itinerary line is written.</p>
      <ul class="ai-bullets">
        <li>Hard guest requirements — always/never rules — are enforced automatically across every leg</li>
        <li>Anchor events lock first: match days, tee times, flights become immovable before routing begins</li>
        <li>Candidate search combines semantic intent, exact-term matching, and concept-based retrieval — surfaces properties that keyword search alone would miss</li>
        <li>Route feasibility, transfer timing, and border logic are validated computationally before assembly</li>
        <li>Every recommendation carries source provenance — traceable to verified, cross-referenced data</li>
        <li>The pipeline stops and asks when it encounters genuine ambiguity. It does not guess.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="agent-grid">
        <span class="a-pill">Brief compiler</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Event locker</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Candidate ranker</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Route feasibility</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Pin selector</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Itinerary architect</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Commercial pricing</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Compliance core</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Contract builder</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Narrative writer</span>
        <span class="a-pill">QA audit gate</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Wetu uploader</span>
        <span class="a-pill">Shopify packager</span>
      </div>
      <p class="sm" style="margin-top:.75rem">14 purpose-built agents. Each has defined inputs, outputs, validation checks, and failure modes.</p>
      <p class="pipeline-note">This is not a prompt sent to a chatbot. It is a governed, gated pipeline — each stage validated before the next begins.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="param-card">
        <div class="pc-title">Planning parameters — example brief</div>
        <div class="param-row"><span class="param-key">Travel style</span><span class="param-val">Luxury · Ultra-luxury · Adventure</span></div>
        <div class="param-row"><span class="param-key">Pace</span><span class="param-val">Relaxed — 3 to 4 nights per stop</span></div>
        <div class="param-row"><span class="param-key">Anchor event</span><span class="param-val anchor">FIFA WC Quarter Final<br>Mexico City · 4 Jul</span></div>
        <div class="param-row"><span class="param-key">Always include</span><span class="param-val">Private game reserve<br>One Relais &amp; Châteaux property</span></div>
        <div class="param-row"><span class="param-key">Never include</span><span class="param-val never">Shared tented camps<br>Dormitory accommodation</span></div>
        <div class="param-row"><span class="param-key">Budget</span><span class="param-val">$800 – $1 200 per person / night</span></div>
      </div>
      <p class="sm" style="margin-top:.85rem;padding-left:.1rem">These parameters become hard constraints applied across every candidate, every leg, and every recommendation — before a single itinerary line is written.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ITINERARY SHOWCASE -->
